1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new chapter to title 37 of the North Dakota Century
2 Code, relating to the establishment of the military compatibility commission.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new chapter to title 37 of the North Dakota Century Code is created and
5 enacted as follows:
6 Definitions.
7 As used in this chapter, "encroachment" means issues that may affect military installation
8 testing, training, and other operations and overall military readiness, including issues related to
9 environmental impact, noise pollution, commercial activities, competition for airspace,
10 competition for radio frequency spectrum, and urban growth around military installations.
11 Military impact zones.
12 A military impact zone is a geographic zone surrounding each military installation in the
13 state, the boundary of which is at least five miles [8.05 kilometers] but no more than twenty-five
14 miles [40.23 kilometers] from the geographic boundary of the military installation. The distance
15 between the boundary of the military impact zone and the:
16 1. Grand Forks air force base is twenty-five miles [40.23 kilometers].
17 2. Minot air force base is twenty-five miles [40.23 kilometers].
18 3. Camp Grafton (South) is five miles [8.05 kilometers] .
19 4. Cavalier space force station is fifteen miles [24.14 kilometers].
20 Military compatibility commission.
21 1. There is created the military compatibility commission to oversee and coordinate land
22 use in military impact zones, prevent encroachment of military installations in military
23 impact zones, and promote the sustainability of military operations in the state.
24 2. The military compatibility commission is composed of:
